Load in Data

data = read.csv('/Users/leighgayle/Box Sync/VE_SD_GIMME_Analysis/Manuscript/Data & Analysis/VE_SD_GIMME_Data_030119_Final.csv')
clean.data = data[-c(3, 62, 130, 174 ), ]
newdata = data[ which(data$Psi_Problem=='0'), ]

Analyses Not Used in Paper

Update on 8.7.2019

After discussion with AB, we decided it’s not appropriate to test the IV vs DV connections because we didn’t run the GIMME multiple solutions option and the incoming vs. outgoing connections could feasibly be reversed. We did decide; however, that node degress (e.g. the total number of connections involving a specific node would be appropriate).
